engineCMS::dbConnect()

Description
    public mixed engineCMS::dbConnect(string $action, mixed $value [, bool $state = FALSE])
    Sets internal values according to action parameter and value parameter.  If the action parameter is set to "database," the function attempts to create a 	 new engineDB object.  If the state parameter is set to FALSE, the function returns the newly created object, $dbObject; otherwise, the newly created 
    object is assigned to the internal openDB object.  Should there be an error opening a new database connection, a FALSE value is returned.

Parameters
    action
	Valid parameters are "username", "password", "port", "server" or "database"
    value
	A valid string or numeric value corresponding appropriately to the action parameter.
    state
	A boolean value of TRUE or FALSE, which determines how the function handles the newly created database object.

Return Values
    TRUE, FALSE or $dbObject.

Examples

	<?php
	    ...
	    $engine->dbConnect("database","enotification", TRUE);
	    ...
	?>
Notes
   
